tein]], confessing regrets for his actions to his former lawyers  [[Lanny Davis]] and [[Lisa Bloom]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Digg Team |title=Email Prankster Strikes Again, Fooling Harvey Weinstein And His Legal Team |url=https://digg.com/2017/harvey-weinstein-lisa-bloom-email-prankster |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater in October, he targeted [[Shark Tank]] personality [[Robert Herjavec]] as the company CEO, inviting him to a toga party. Later the fake account was copied into official financial projection documents.<ref name=\"buzzfeed\" />\n\nFinally in late October, UK [[National Cyber Security Centre (United Kingdom)|National Cyber Security Centre]] technical director Ian Levy was targeted with a fake industry event, however Levy correctly identified the unexpected headers.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Levy |first1=Ian |title=The serious side of pranking |url=https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/serious-side-pranking |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=30 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Other pranks ==\n* [[Kevin Spacey]], American actor, producer, and singer\n* Alan Stewart, CFO [[Tesco]] as [[John Allan (businessman)|John Allan]], CEO Tesco\n* [[Dennis Muilenburg]], CEO, [[Boeing]] as [[Ed Liddy]], Board Member of Boeing\n* [[Norman Tebbit]], UK Politician as [[Boris Johnson]], then Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs. Fake Johnson told Tebbit to \"go fuck yourself\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gray |first1=Jasmin |title=Anthony Scaramucci Sent Some Seriously Bizarre Emails To A Prankster Pretending To Be Reince Priebus |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/anthony-scaramucci-emails-prankster-pretending-reince-priebus_uk_59803a43e4b00bb8ff393655?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAABWxAJdRPEx5U6LWSe7EylppVsWv2paMsz6yDJ4fYWcmQGO7M2gCP-tchRnnlSdQYM1fElRm_wuAimXwDH38Yfj5h1jZvs-cAGxkbcVelJXkBzZBWbpUZbowB5kGNii5jAZSeRZ3arT_zratqmgS_t_N79N6DZ5k12-Oh2YXBYgI |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</